main event: A long object the size of a plane was observed at night in Des Plaines, Illinois.
interesting points: The object appeared as a bright white light and revolved for a period of 10 seconds., The object flew lower than a plane and descended to the West at 650 mph., The observation lasted for about 4 minutes., The witness stated that the data presented could not have been an aircraft., The event was documented by the 928th Troop Carrier Group, Medium (Reserve) of the United States Air Force.
sighted object: a long object the size of a plane emitting a bright white light
witness description: documented by United States Air Force officials
